						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the central shrine in the Varadarāja-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is also fragmentary.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 4[0] sheep to provide for a lamp in the temple of the god Tiruvāyppāḍidēvan in a certain <hi rend="italic">maṅgalam</hi> (full name not clear), for the merit of a certain Chittirakūṭa Muttarāmappaṉ Vaḍugaṉ Maḻapāḍi who died of an accident (?).</p>						

						</summary>
